Peru Stocks: Atacocha, Austral, Cementos Lima, Ferreyros, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-04-04T17:03:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/peru-stocks-atacocha-austral-cementos-lima-ferreyros-volcan.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 12:36 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index fell 1.3 percent to 21,276.33. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index slid 0.8 percent to 2,889.09.  Industrial stocks slumped after a poll published by Lima-
based research Ipsos Apoyo showed opposition presidential
candidate Ollanta Humala widening his lead before the April 10
elections, said Miguel Pancorvo, head trader at Lima-based
brokerage Compass SAB. Humala has said he will renegotiate
contracts with foreign companies if he’s elected.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1)  (FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor for
Caterpillar Inc., fell 4.2 percent to 3.45 soles.  Cementos Lima
SA (CEMLIMI1)  (CEMLIMC1 PE), the country’s biggest cement maker, dropped
3.9 percent to 37 soles. Austral Group SA (AUSTRAC1 PE), a unit
of Austevoll Seafood ASA, fell 3.2 percent to 30 centimos. Corp.
Aceros Arequipa SA (CORAREI1 PE), the Lima-based steelmaker,
slid 2.5 percent to 3.09 soles.  Copper and silver miners dropped after metals declined in
New York and  London .  Volcan Cia Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest silver
producer, fell 3.3 percent to 3.77 soles. Sociedad Minera Cerro
Verde SA (CVERDEC1 PE), a unit of Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold
Inc., fell 2.6 percent to $43.82. Cia. Minera Atacocha SA
(ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based silver and zinc producer, fell 2.4
percent to 1.20 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
